  "body": "In our current implementation, creating a genesis state from eth1 gets slower and slower the more deposits are accumulated. This is because we naively recreate a new genesis deposit tree and state in every call to [`checkGenesis`](https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/master/packages/lodestar/src/chain/chain.ts#L218).\r\n\r\nWe ideally would maintain a genesis deposit tree and beacon state that we incrementally update with each new timestamp, eth1Data, and depositDatas.\r\nThis requires reworking the logic in [`initializeBeaconStateFromEth1`](https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/blob/master/packages/lodestar/src/chain/genesis/genesis.ts#L32). We will still need `initializeBeaconStateFromEth1` to remain, to be used to test genesis in spec tests, but we won't be using the all-at-once `initializeBeaconStateFromEth1`, directly, in our beacon node.",
